Spreadtrum Jumps Most in Two Months in New York on Sales Outlook

-- B y   Z a c h a r y   T r a c e r
-- 
2011-12-08T14:50:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-08/spreadtrum-jumps-most-in-two-months-in-new-york-on-sales-outlook.html
Spreadtrum Communications Inc. (SPRD) , a
Chinese mobile-phone chipmaker, surged the most in two months in
 New York  after saying revenue may exceed forecasts.  Spreadtrum American depositary receipts gained 7.6 percent
to $22.30 at 9:47 a.m. in New York after earlier soaring as much
as 8.5 percent, the most intraday since Oct. 4. Spreadtrum,
based in Shanghai, said in a statement today it is “on track to
meet or exceed” its fourth-quarter revenue forecast of $188
million to $194 million.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zachary Tracer in New York at 
 ztracer1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  